{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01DiE4eRRh9A21fZfxiih7hN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me mark the first task done and plan my migration approach. This is a Jakarta EE application with:\n- JSF (JavaServer Faces) frontend with XHTML templates\n- EJB (Enterprise Java Beans) for business logic\n- JPA entities for persistence\n- Open Liberty application server\n- H2 in-memory database\n\nThe migration to Spring Boot will:\n1. Replace JSF with Thymeleaf templates (or REST API endpoints)\n2. Replace EJB with Spring `@Service` / `@Component` beans\n3. Keep JPA entities (Spring Boot uses Jakarta Persistence)\n4. Replace Open Liberty with embedded Tomcat (Spring Boot default)\n5. Move from WAR to JAR packaging\n6. Expose REST endpoints to match the functionality\n\nSince the original app is a JSF web app, I'll create REST API endpoints that expose the same business logic, plus simple Thymeleaf templates for the UI. Let me begin the migration."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6744,"cache_read_input_tokens":44110,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":6744,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":722},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"263c0197-604d-4139-b6dd-23a5ef8a48e5","uuid":"c56e55c4-5244-448f-8b8b-67830ba53797"}
